    },
    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:1.1",
          "pli": "“Imaṃ, bhikkhave, rattiṃ aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, bhikkhave, sā devatā maṃ etadavoca: ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, tonight, a glorious deity, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, came to me, bowed, stood to one side, and said to me: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:1.2",
          "pli": "‘sattime, bhante, dhammā bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattanti. ",
          "en": "‘Sir, these seven things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:1.3",
          "pli": "Katame satta? ",
          "en": "What seven? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:1.4",
          "pli": "Satthugāravatā, dhammagāravatā, saṅghagāravatā, sikkhāgāravatā, samādhigāravatā, hirigāravatā, ottappagāravatā. ",
          "en": "Respect for the Teacher, for the teaching, for the Saṅgha, for the training, for immersion, for conscience, and for prudence. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:1.5",
          "pli": "Ime kho, bhante, satta dhammā bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattantī’ti. ",
          "en": "These seven things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:1.6",
          "pli": "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, sā devatā. ",
          "en": "That is what that deity said. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:1.7",
          "pli": "Idaṃ vatvā maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyīti. ",
          "en": "Then he bowed and respectfully circled me, keeping me on his right side, before vanishing right there. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:2.1",
          "pli": "Satthugaru dhammagaru, ",
          "en": "Respect for the Teacher and the teaching, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:2.2",
          "pli": "saṅghe ca tibbagāravo; ",
          "en": "and keen respect for the Saṅgha; "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:2.3",
          "pli": "Samādhigaru ātāpī, ",
          "en": "respect for immersion, being energetic, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:2.4",
          "pli": "sikkhāya tibbagāravo. ",
          "en": "and keen respect for the training. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:3.1",
          "pli": "Hiriottappasampanno, ",
          "en": "One with both conscience and prudence, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:3.2",
          "pli": "sappatisso sagāravo; ",
          "en": "reverential and respectful, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:3.3",
          "pli": "Abhabbo parihānāya, ",
          "en": "can’t decline, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:3.4",
          "pli": "nibbānasseva santike”ti. ",
          "en": "and has drawn near to extinguishment.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an7.33:3.5",
          "pli": "Dutiyaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
